The paper is about a method for optimizing software configurations, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The method uses machine learning techniques to sequentially explore the configuration space, which suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of programming languages (cs.PL) and distributed computing (cs.DC) in the evaluation of the method. Finally, the paper discusses the application of the method to software systems, which suggests a connection to systems and control (cs.SY).
